oai_dc:dc.dc:title: 1903 Memphis Levee
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: levees; cobblestones; riverboats;
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Note on the back of the photo reads, "View of Memphis Levee in 1903 - high water. This shows the old horse watering trough and the river gauge attended to by Capt. John Harris, Reuben A. Harris, and John Harris, Jr. from 1900-1916.
